[size=4][u]Changelog[/u][/size]

[size=3][u][b][1.08] - 2025-05-11[/b][/u][/size]

[size=3][u][i]Added[/i][/u][/size]
[list]
[*] Internal ([b]experimental[/b]) station attack order. Written from scratch positioning ships against stations, including reaction on stations drones attacks in non-OOS mode. Works only for fleets with [b]L[/b] and [b]XL[/b] ships. For only [b]L[/b] ships - four and more ships are recommended.
[*] Possibility to select station attack order - by default it is [b]Coordinate attack[/b]. Other possibilities are [b]usual[/b] one and [b]experimental[/b] one.
[*] Additional confirmation for the working in hazardous regions, like [b]The Void[/b]. Please be aware - the order will stop working in the sectors with the hazardous regions without the confirmation.
[*] Own icons for the [b]Protect Sector[/b] and [b]Station attack[/b] orders.
[/list]
[size=3][u][i]Improved[/i][/u][/size]
[list]
[*] Fully rewritten the logic of idling and scanning for enemy ships. Now it is more precise.
[*] Implemented workaround for the repairing/restocking ships. By default Player owned ships can be repaired only in current sector.
[/list]
[size=3][u][i]Fixed[/i][/u][/size]
[list]
[*] Fixed a reaction on attack on player's ships/stations by enemy drones.
[*] Accidentally attacks from the non-enemies are not considered as an attack on the player ships/stations.
[/list]
[size=3][u][b][1.07] - 2025-03-16[/b][/u][/size]

[size=3][u][i]Added[/i][/u][/size]
[list]
[*] [b]By negative relation[/b] to set the relation to possible targets more precisely.
[*] [b]Park exactly there[/b] to set the exact position where the ship should park when it is not targets to fight against. Useful for big sectors.
[/list]
[size=3][u][i]Improved[/i][/u][/size]
[list]
[*] Idle flying when any parking is not set.
[*] Attack of the stations via [b]Coordinate attack[/b] in now visible, as it is run not as a script, but as an order.
[/list]
[size=3][u][b][1.06] - 2025-03-01[/b][/u][/size]

[size=3][u][i]Fixed[/i][/u][/size]
[list]
[*] The Lost Ship Replacement not always works correctly.
[/list]
[size=3][u][b][1.05] - 2025-03-01[/b][/u][/size]

[size=3][u][i]Added[/i][/u][/size]
[list]
[*] Support for the [b]Lost Ship Replacement[/b] feature of version [b]7.50[/b]
[*] Added additional parameter to set a threshold from moving to target to attack it. In percentage of the radar range.
[/list]
[size=3][u][i]Fixed[/i][/u][/size]
[list]
[*] For version [b]7.50[/b] and higher, boosters are used always, despite the [b]Avoid boosters usage[/b] option.
[*] The default value for [b]Disable on destruction threat[/b] is [b]0 percent[/b] - i.e. disabled this check.
[/list]
